Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I'll admit, I was a bit lucky. I didn't have rich parents. My mom didn't didn't go to school. My dad passed away young. The only option had in life was to become successful because nobody around me was.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia Let me not get off track though. Here's a quick rundown of my corporate career. -Merrill Lynch in 2008 -Tesla in 2015 -Google in 2017 -Facebook in 2018 continued...'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia When first started out in corporate @ Merrill Lynch, realized how EVERYONE was broke. Most of my peers would drive their BMW to work in Gucci Loafers and still be paycheck-to-paycheck paycheck-to While they're making $100k+ That's when to invest. realized that I needed'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia Sol did... It sounds simple enough, but it took a lot of work. I saved and invested as much as possible (which wasn't easy because I hao a kid at 19). I ended going all-in on rea estate starting in 2011.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I bought three properties in 2011, and then the other five properties were purchased over the next nine years In total, my portfolio was worth ~$6.7M when I retired and it was composed of over 50 units.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I didn't invest crazy amounts into any of these either. I primarily used the BRRRR strategy and kept buying undervalued multifamily properties in Miami for dirt cheap. The cash flow from these properties alone allowed me to retire.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I knew could live comfortably off of $20,000/m. As of 2019, my properties were cash flowing about the same (net). That's when I knew I could retire.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richard Garcia @richardgarcia I didn't nvest because it was the "cool thing to do" It took a lot of sacrifices, long weekends, and long nights to get to this point. But it's all all worth it because now I can do whatever want with my time.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @richardgarciaofficial. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Richaro Garcia @richardgarcia I'm here to share the lessons I've learned while building an $8M real estate portfolio. Not too many people have this much skin in the game on social media and you get to see my wins and losses in real-time. If you want to join me in my investing journey, follow me.'.

Photo shared by The #1 Investment Page📈 on September 18, 2021 tagging @basharjkatou. May be an image of 1 person, beard and text that says '-You wake up without an alarm -You are in no rush. -You plan out your day. -No traffic jams. -You work on your own terms. -You can take a break at any time. -Read or excercise when you want to. THAT'S FINANCIAL FREEDOM. @basharjkatou'.
